\begin_layout Subsection
Shortcuts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Well known shortcuts are already available in Lyx.
 For example use Ctrl+C to copy selected text and Ctrl+V to paste selected
 text.
 To copy a table from a spreadsheet inside a Lyx table, use Ctrl+Shift+V,
 this will preserve some elements of formatting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Menu actions can be mapped to create new keyboard shortcuts.
 This can be very useful for actions used frequently.
 For example citation insert can be mapped to Ctrl+Alt+C (or another key
 combination if your prefer).
 Under 
\family sans
Tools\SpecialChar \menuseparator
Preferences \SpecialChar \menuseparator
Editing\SpecialChar \menuseparator
Shortcuts
\family default
 show key-binding containing 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

citation
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Then click on it to change the key combination.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Document export
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lyx is mostly used to generate articles and reports in PDF format.
 Lyx documents can also be exported to html or rich text format (compatible
 with microsoft word).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is important to note that Lyx documents can be exported to Latex.
 The underlying Latex can be displayed at all times from the View/Source
 pane menu.
\end_layout

